class Solution {
    public int integerReplacement(int n) {
        int steps = 0;
        while (n != 1) {
            if ((n & 1) == 0) {
                n >>>= 1;
            } else if (n == 3 || Integer.bitCount(n + 1) > Integer.bitCount(n - 1)) {
                n--;
            } else {
                n++;
            }
            steps++;
        }
        return steps;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Iterative bit-level approach that halves even numbers and chooses the path that reduces set bits for odd numbers, avoiding recursion and memoization overhead.

